{
  "text": "Although we classify constants rather than theorems (this distinction is less pronounced in intuitionistic type theory [CITATION_1] ), we assume in the following definition that the theorems are also assigned to a positive and negative set of theorems. After the strategy terminates, a theorem will be said to be in the positive set if it has a score greater than 0 and in the negative set if its score is 0. We can then state a similar constraint relation between theorems and constants that we call constant coherence.",
